Key Match Events: France won 1-0 against Belgium in the Euro 2024 round of 16.
Randal Kolo Muani scored the only goal of the match.
Kevin De Bruyne had a chance towards the end but couldn't score.
Belgium's defensive play was a surprise to France.
Post-Match Reflections: France coach Didier Deschamps praised the team's performance and emphasized the importance of reaching the quarter-finals.
Randal Kolo Muani expressed joy over the win and mentioned his coach's advice to bring energy and speed.
Belgian captain Kevin De Bruyne expressed disappointment over the loss and mentioned the team's efforts.
Belgium coach Domenico Tedesco stated that they will analyze the games and the tournament in a few weeks.
France's Jules Kounde, the player of the match, highlighted the team's comprehensive game and his competitive spirit.
Belgian goalkeeper Koen Casteels described the tournament as middling and expressed disappointment.
